article.description: Courtney Vandersloot had 22 points and 13 assists, leading No. 23 Gonzaga to a 106-66 victory over Saint Mary's.
article.headline: Gonzaga clears 100 points for second straight game
article.story:
SPOKANE, Wash. --  Courtney Vandersloot had 22 points and 13 assists, leading No. 23 Gonzaga to a 106-66 victory over Saint Mary's on Thursday night.

Janelle Bekkering also had 22 points for the Bulldogs (25-4, 13-0 West Coast Conference), who shot 55 percent from the field. Kayla Standish added 19 points and 13 rebounds, and Katelan Redmon finished with 15 points.

Vandersloot also had six steals and no turnovers as high-scoring Gonzaga cleared 100 points for the second straight game and seventh time this season.

Jasmine Smith scored 24 for Saint Mary's (17-11, 9-4), which committed 28 turnovers. Louella Tomlinson had 10 points and blocked four shots.

The Bulldogs opened the second half with a 14-2 run to take a 64-35 lead with 15:34 left. Standish capped the surge with a jumper.
